"{\"uid\": \"nbcnewyork.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-katie-ledecky-swimming-paris-olympics-history-next-race-5655365\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Here are five things to know about the legend who many consider to be the best female swimmer of all time.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky, already considered one of the greatest swimmers of all time, could make more history at the Paris Olympics and set the record for the most gold medals by an American woman.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 0.9999999887018022, \"rank\": 6.043733298370321e-09, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After winning the 1500m freestyle and earning her eighth gold medal and twelfth overall medal, she is now tied with swimmer Jenny Thompson, Dara Torres and Natalie Coughlin for the most overall Olympic medals.\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 421, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dara Torres\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\"}, {\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natalie Coughlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also tied Thompson for most gold medals by an American woman.\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9887509805818867, \"rank\": 0.01137699949523053, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 0.9999999887018022, \"rank\": 6.043733298370321e-09, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One more gold medal and she would separate herself into a new tier as the most decorated U.S. woman in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch NBC 4 free wherever you are  Her next race is expected to be on Thursday, August 1 at 4:03 p.m. ETin the women's 4x200 freestyle relay.\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 701, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.8439759979540433, \"rank\": 0.18439115690027125, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For anyone who has watched Ledecky over her career, they know not to doubt that anything is possible.\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch all the action from the Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games live on Peacock  Ledecky is expected to competein thewomen's 4x200 freestyle relayon Thursday, Aug. 1, at 4:03 p.m.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999740404316403, \"rank\": 2.5960242368634875e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.99754396392687, \"rank\": 0.00246203271322362, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky is also slated torace in the second heatfor the women's 800m freestyle on Friday, Aug. 2, at around 5:52 a.m.\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If she qualifies, Ledecky will race in the women's 800m freestyle gold medal event on Saturday, Aug. 3, at around 3:08 p.m.  Katie Ledeckyis expected to compete in four Olympics events in Paris.\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999740404316403, \"rank\": 2.5960242368634875e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has a total of 12 Olympic medals, with eight of them gold, three silver and one bronze.\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has competed in four Olympics, the first being London in 2012, where she won a gold medal in the women's 800m freestyle atthe age of 15.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999452923035, \"rank\": 3.5161357394622854e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2016, Ledecky won four gold medals, all for freestyle events (women's 200m, 400m, 800m freestyle and the 4x200m freestyle relay), as well as a silver in the women's 4x100m freestyle relay.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, Ledecky won two gold medals (women's 800m and 1500m freestyle) and two silver medals (women's 400m freestyle and 4x200m freestyle relay).\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1880, \"end\": 1885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9995644902849209, \"rank\": 0.0004356971772076645, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So far, in Paris, Ledecky has won a gold in the women's 1500m freestyle and a bronze in the women's 400m freestyle.\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999740404316403, \"rank\": 2.5960242368634875e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky is from Bethesda,Maryland, beloved in the area and from the same state as fellow Olympics legend Michael Phelps.\", \"from\":